{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Miniatures, Maps, and Virtual Tabletops\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Movement and positioning in hand-to-hand combat are challenging elements to keep track of in roleplaying games. While some players and gamemasters are less concerned with particulars during combat, some feel the need to keep track of the relative positions of the player characters and their adversaries. Using figures, tokens, or markers on a map can answer any questions, presenting a concrete means of determining what is happening and where.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Roleplaying miniatures are small plastic or metallic statuettes about several centimeters high, available at most game and hobby stores or online. There is an enormous variety of character types, costumes, genres, historical periods, and poses, and collecting, assembling, and painting miniatures is a pleasant side hobby.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To keep track of movement, maps with grids of squares or hexagons are often useful. These come in sheets of various sizes made of paper or sturdier materials. Stores that carry miniature figures also probably carry these. Some players dislike grids as rigid, confining, or mechanistic, and prefer to eyeball distances and negotiate movement, using rulers or tape measures as last resorts. You may want to experiment, to see what suits you. A gamemaster who uses miniatures or maps will want a few larger sheets of paper to use for sketching out floor plans and creating simple maps. Players may find graph paper useful in mapping ruins or buildings. Mapmaking programs specialized for roleplaying games make this increasingly easy, and pre-made maps and tile sets are readily available.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Online tabletops allow for entire game sessions to be played online, with gamemaster tools, player storage of character sheets, and battle maps that also have sound effects, lighting, dice rolling apps, and even more, letting gamemasters and players automate this aspect of play and allow for immersive play with players anywhere they can use their computers. These range from top-down simple map programs to 3D environments, customizable by the gamemaster, with \u8216'modules\u8217' of content available, including adventure and other aspects useful to play.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 A Combat Example\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The following example is set in a fantasy world and describes how the warrior Yvarre has stolen a priceless amulet from the treasure chamber of a sinister cult of serpent-worshippers and is trying to escape the temple to where her ally Kallistor is waiting.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 First Combat Round\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Tucking the enormous jewel-studded golden amulet into her waistband, Yvarre slips out of the cult\u8217's treasure room and silently moves down the passage beyond, hoping to avoid notice while she gets to where her friend Kallistor waits with a couple of horses.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 As she moves down the corridor, a dagger is thrown at Yvarre from behind. The gamemaster rolls a success and says that Yvarre has been struck high on her left shoulder (the optional hit location system is not being used. this is just the gamemaster elaborating with flavor in their description). The gamemaster rolls 1D4+2+1D2, the damage that the dagger does plus half the thrower\u8217's damage modifier. Luckily for Yvarre, the gamemaster gets a 4 on the damage roll, the lowest possible result.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yvarre wears a soft leather tunic (armor value 1) and has 17 hit points. Her armor protects her from 1 point of damage, so Yvarre loses 3 hit points, not 4. She\u8217's now down to 14 hit points, so her player carefully crosses out the numbers 17,16, and 15, and circles the 14 on Yvarre\u8217's character sheet.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 She glances back and sees a serpent priest drawing another dagger from his sleeve as he approaches.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Second Combat Round\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Cursing at her bad luck, Yvarre enters the chamber and bolts the door behind her, then reaches around to examine her wound. Fortunately, the attack was not an impaling one, so the blade is not stuck deeply in her shoulder. Next, she attempts to treat the wound with First Aid. Yvarre\u8217's First Aid skill is 47%: her player rolls a 99\u8212-a fumble!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A roll on the fumble table is not necessary: the penalty for a fumble with First Aid is always the loss of 1 hit point of damage. The gamemaster says that Yvarre did herself an extra point of damage in pulling at the wound, due to the awkward location. The wound is wider now, and blood from it drenches the back of her soft leather tunic (again, this is not a result of a special damage result: it\u8217's just flavor for the players to help them visualize the scene).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yvarre\u8217's player sighs and crosses off another hit point. Yvarre now has 13 hit points.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Third Combat Round\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Muffled thuds come from the bolted door. Yvarre wheels and goes to the window through which she entered. She takes hold of the rope she had hung there, preparing to climb down. The gamemaster holds up a hand to halt the player\u8217's description and injects, \u8220"Yvarre notices that the rope feels very light. Does she want to see why?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 She does, the player says, and has Yvarre pull up the line. Yvarre\u8217's escape rope ends a meter beneath the sill. It has been cut, likely by someone leaning out the window below.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yvarre is trapped unless she decides to jump to the street. The gamemaster says, \u8220"Make a Spot roll to find out if Yvarre notices something.\u8221" In this case, the \u8216'something\u8217' the gamemaster is referring to is a cult assassin on the roof top opposite Yvarre, readying his bow for an attack.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The player rolls D100 for Yvarre\u8217's Spot skill and fails. Since Yvarre doesn\u8217't notice the cult assassin, the gamemaster rolls 43, a hit, and then rolls for damage, 1D8+1, but no damage modifier. The gamemaster rolls 9 in damage, which will be reduced by 1 for Yvarre\u8217's armor. \u8220"Is that enough for a major wound?\u8221" the gamemaster inquires. The player nods glumly. She marks off 8 more hit points on her character sheet, lowering her remaining hit points to 5.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yvarre\u8217's player rolls on the major wound table, getting a result of 27, and the gamemaster says that the arrow struck Yvarre in the left arm. Yvarre\u8217's Luck roll succeeds, so the wound will not become a permanent injury. Yvarre feels herself weakening, the gamemaster says. She\u8217'll become unconscious in four combat rounds, one round for each hit point she currently possesses.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 At the other end of the room, the door to the hallway is beginning to splinter. Yvarre could use the next round to try to apply First Aid to this new wound, but she can\u8217't afford the time.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Fourth Combat Round\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If Yvarre stays in the room, she\u8217'll soon be at the mercy of the serpent-worshipping cult, not something to look forward to. It\u8217's 6 meters down to the ground, and Yvarre\u8217's player realizes that in her condition the fall could kill her. However, the player also knows that Yvarre herself would never hesitate. \u8220"I jump,\u8221" she says. The archer takes another shot. Missile fire cannot be dodged, so Yvarre hopes for the best. She\u8217's in luck\u8212-the arrow misses.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Make your Jump roll, please.\u8221" The result is a 21, a success. \u8220"Okay\u8221", says the gamemaster, \u8220"now roll 1D6 for the damage reduction.\u8221" She gets a 3, to be subtracted from any damage incurred in the fall to come. \u8220"And now roll 2D6 for the fall damage.\u8221" Her dice total 5. Yvarre had 5 hit points. She loses 5, but the successful Jump roll saves 3. Yvarre now has 2 hit points left.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 At 2 hit points, Yvarre automatically falls unconscious. This is not more than half her total hit points, so there is no new major wound.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Fifth Combat Round\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In the night-black alley, Yvarre\u8217's friend Kallistor hears her hit the ground and finds her motionless on the cobblestones. Listening to the approaching shouts, Kallistor\u8217's player decides to throw Yvarre across the saddle of one horse and mount the other, fleeing immediately.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Sixth Combat Round\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A few streets distant, Kallistor feels safe enough to stop for a round. He uses the magic spell Healing 1 on Yvarre\u8217's knife wound. Kallistor\u8217's spell restores 3 hit points to Yvarre (a roll of 3 on 1D6) and the gamemaster rules that Yvarre is now conscious and able to ride but is very weak. Kallistor\u8217's player marks off 3 power points for the use of the spell (which costs 3 power points per level used). Kallistor has 14 power points, so it puts him down to 11.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Several Combat Rounds Later\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 After some evasive riding through town to prevent followers, the gamemaster says that no pursuit is evident. The two adventurers reach their hideout. Inside, safe for the moment, Kallistor uses First Aid to try to heal the arrow wound, raising her hit points to 7.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Next Combat Round\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Yvarre also took fall damage. Kallistor\u8217's First Aid was for the knife wound, but Yvarre\u8217's First Aid roll works on the general bruising from the fall. The 2 points of fall damage are erased. The injury is still present, but no longer has practical consequence. Now Yvarre is at 9 hit points.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Next Combat Round after That\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Kallistor\u8217's unsuccessful First Aid attempt fails to heal the dagger damage, as has Yvarre\u8217's previous attempt.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 One More Combat Round\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Kallistor uses Healing 2 on Yvarre\u8217's arrow wound, restoring 4 points out of a possible 12. Yvarre is now at 13 hit points, and Kallistor is now down 6 more power points, leaving him at 5 power points total. Neither of them is in dire shape, but Yvarre is not at full hit points and Kallistor has used up several power points.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The dagger wound will heal naturally in a week, and the remaining damage from the arrow wound will take at least two weeks. Kallistor wants to keep some power points in reserve in case of emergency. He\u8217'll try the spell later, when he\u8217's got more power points or when the coast is clear.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 After Combat\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 At this point, there is little reason to continue using combat time, so everyone switches into narrative time in which the player behavior and gamemaster narration becomes more relaxed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Her wounds and injuries attended to for the moment, Yvarre reaches into her waistband to pull out the amulet. It seems to twist in her hands, as she does so, so she lets it go. As it hits the ground, the amulet breaks into dozens of tiny jewel-eyed golden snakes that fall to the ground and slither away.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All that, and for nothing!\par}
