{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Vehicles\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Just as with weapons and armor types, the following section includes a variety of vehicles listed in {\b Movement Rates}, as well as others suitable for adventuring. These abstract examples can help you and your gamemaster create additional types of vehicles, expanding or altering statistics as desired.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The following terms are used to define each vehicle:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Type:} The generic type of vehicle.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Skill:} The skill to use when piloting it.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Rated Speed:} The maximum speed of the vehicle, an abstract value used in the chase system.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Handling:} The modifier applied to your character\u8217's skill, reflecting the vehicle\u8217's maneuverability or relative ease of use.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b ACC:} Acceleration, the number of speed increments the vehicle can accelerate or decelerate from its current rated speed each combat round. This is provided as a value of \u177 ?, and is used in the vehicle chase system.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b MOV:} The maximum speed of the vehicle in a combat round, expressed in its MOV rating. MOV has a sliding value of 1\u8211-5 meters; this assumes a median value of 3.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Armor:} The vehicle\u8217's general armor value and protection it provides to crew or passengers. Usually, attacks on passengers are through a window or open section of the cabin. If these two numbers are different, they are expressed as two values separated by a slash. Your gamemaster should determine whether a character has protection from the vehicle. Attacking someone within a vehicle is {\i Difficult}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b SIZ:} The vehicle\u8217's apparent SIZ value.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b HP:} The vehicle\u8217's hit points. Vehicles do not suffer the secondary effects of special successes, other than increased damage, and critical successes ignore the vehicle\u8217's armor and do increased damage.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Crew:} The number of characters required to pilot and maintain the vehicle at full efficiency while enroute. For larger vessels, this is usually 1/3 the normal complement, as the crews work in 8-hour shifts. Vehicle-related skill rolls may be {\i Difficult} if the vehicle is under-crewed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Passengers:} The number of passengers the vehicle normally carries, combined with the number of off-duty crewmembers (if appropriate).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Cargo:} The space the vehicle has for cargo, expressed in SIZ. For game purposes, 1 ENC equals 1 SIZ point.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Value:} A general value for the vehicle, as described in {\b Money} and {\b Purchasing Equipment}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Notes:} Additional notes about the vehicle and its capabilities.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Vehicle Descriptions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This section describes a variety of vehicles, organized alphabetically.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Air Vehicle, Bomber:} A huge, propeller or turbine-driven aircraft utilized for long-range bombing missions, usually equipped with several machinegun turrets.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Air Vehicle, Dirigible:} A balloon with a limited structural framework and a small cabin hanging below, usually inflated with a lighter-than air gas. Driven by rotors.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Air Vehicle, Helicopter:} A smallish rotary blade-powered air vehicle. Cabins range from simple plexiglass bubbles to armored with troop compartments and gun mounts.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Air Vehicle, Jet:} A long commercial jet airliner, with at least two wingmounted jet turbines.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Air Vehicle, Jet Fighter:} A relatively small, highly maneuverable jet designed for aerial combat and bombing strikes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Air Vehicle, Propeller Plane:} A small propeller-driven passenger plane.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Air Vehicle, Skyskimmer:} A hightech ultralight air vehicle capable of vertical takeoff and landing, utilizing advanced thruster technology.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Automobile, Modern Sedan:} An average four-door modern automobile.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Automobile, Modern Sportscar:} An extremely fast, two-door, two-seat, high-performance automobile.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Automobile, Vintage:} An old boxy automobile, equivalent to the Model\u8211-T.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Boat, Motor:} A smallish motorboat with a single propeller and a small forward cabin.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Boat, Small Rowed:} A small two-bench rowboat.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Chariot:} A small two-horse chariot, with room for one driver, one warrior, and a small rack for weapons or personal effects.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Four-Horse Carriage:} An open or cloth-top four-horse carriage.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Four-Horse Wagon:} A wooden stagecoach with a cramped passenger cabin and room for storage on back and on top.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Horse:} See {\i Chapter 11: Creatures}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Hovercraft:} A commercial hovercraft ferry suitable for around 20 passengers on relatively still water.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Land Skimmer:} A high-tech turbine-driven land vehicle that skims on a bed of compressed air, like a hovercraft.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Motorcycle:} A two-wheeled motor vehicle with room for a driver and one passenger. Sidecar optional.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Ship, Aircraft Carrier:} An immense ship (300+ meters long) with a flat deck capable of launching fighter craft and having them land on it.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Ship, Ancient Rowed:} A longship with single rows of oars port and starboard, usually rowed by galley slaves or by fighting men.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Ship, Modern Battle}: A massive battleship (165+ meters long), heavily armored with a wide variety of longrange artillery and missile systems.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Ship, Modern Cruise:} A massive passenger liner (300+ meters long) serving almost as a mobile hotel, with shops, entertainment facilities, and countless amenities.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Ship, Vintage Sailing:} A galleon, roughly 35 meters in length, with two or more masts.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Space Vehicle, Cargo:} The mainstay of space commerce, this is a cargo vessel with a small crew. Lightly armored and armed. May have energy shielding.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Space Vehicle, Rocket:} A multi-stage fuelled rocket with a small passenger cabin/landing module.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Space Vehicle, Starfighter:} A relatively small, highly maneuverable spaceship equivalent to a jet fighter. Heavily armed, though lightly armored. May have energy shielding.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Space Vehicle, Transport:} A moderate-sized spaceship used primarily for passenger or cargo transport, lightly armored and armed. May have energy shielding.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Submarine:} A submersible vessel used by the military for stealth, infiltration of enemy waters, and naval combat.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Tank, Modern:} A heavily armored tracked combat vehicle equipped with a large-caliber central gun as well as other armaments.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Tank, Vintage:} A heavily-armored tracked combat vehicle, usually equipped with a large-caliber central gun.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Train, Bullet:} A high-speed, streamlined passenger train built on a specialized track, usually driven by electricity.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Train, Mag\u8211-lev:} A train levitating on a magnetic track.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Train, Steam Engine:} A steamdriven engine dating from the later 1800s. SIZ value is per car.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Truck, Pickup:} A four-wheel drive pickup truck.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Truck, Semi (18-wheeler):} A large commercial truck with a small cabin and a long cargo compartment.\par}
