{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Attacks (hybrid form):}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Bite 50%, 1D4+\u189 ?dm (bleeding)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Claws 65%, 1D6+dm (bleeding)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Attacks (wolf form):}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Bite 65%, 1D8+\u189 ?dm (bleeding)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Claws 45%, 1D6+dm (bleeding)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In either form, a werewolf can make one bite attack and two claw attacks each combat round.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Powers:} Werewolves have the following powers:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Immunity:} Werewolves are immune to most forms of damage other than magic, fire, or silver. Other attacks simply bounce off, regardless of the result. Magic, fire, and silvered weapons do full damage. A weapon with a spell cast upon it, such as Sorcerer\u8217's Razor, does its magical damage but not the weapon\u8217's damage or the attacker\u8217's damage modifier. An outright magical weapon does normal damage. The gamemaster should determine if energy weapons or other similar attacks can damage a werewolf.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Regeneration:} Werewolves can regenerate 1 hit point each combat round unless that damage was done with a silver weapon. Werewolves heal from damage inflicted by a silver weapon at their normal healing rate.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Transformation:} Werewolves can assume one of three different forms; human, hybrid, and wolf. Shifting from one shape to another takes 5 DEX ranks and costs no power points. The werewolf can switch from any of these forms to another.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Skills:} Climb 75%, Dodge 65%, Hide 60%, Jump 80%, Listen 70%, Sense 90%, Spot 70%, Track 90%.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Zombie\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Zombies are animated corpses resurrected by necromancy, voodoo, demonic possession, or modern causes such as toxic chemicals, radiation, or biological plague. Whatever their origin, zombies thirst for human flesh (some prefer brains) and do little else than seek to feed. Zombies are usually incapable of speech and stalk the living in mobs. They are not particularly bright and are easily fooled.\par}
